Exercise 2: Learning Outcomes
In this activity I learnt how to achieve a goal, both for short term and long term.
This activity helped me to understand four pillars for Target Achievement, that
are Strength, Weakness, Threats, and Opportunities and I looked at my targets
through this four windows.
This activity taught me how see myself unbiasly and thoroughly inspecting all
four parameters in me and my life.
Compare to my previous activity, this time I was little bit more confident and
more engaging for my audience, which some what build my character.
As last time I conveyed in Hinglish (Hindi + English), this time it was compulsory
to convey in English only, which improved my English speaking quality.
Sanket Palwe, Department of Engineering, Sciences and Humanities, VIT, Pune-37 10
Exercise 3: Interpersonal Skill Development: Positive Relationship, Positive
Attitudes, Handling Situations: Conversational and Action script
In this activity, we performed a act to develop mentioned skills that is we perform
a short role play on Kota Suicide Cases. As this topic was very sensitive and
disturbing, we had to plan very finely, accurately and ensure every scene is well
performed. In this activity we throwed light on Dark Coaching System, and on all
toxic coaching owners, we showcased life of JEE students studying day and night,
Studying for their family expectations, burning their minds in this heavy
competitions, we also showcased how they are misguided by greedy coaching
owners, continuously dreaming them about IITs, so that they can feel their
pockets.
Through this activity we also potrayed who are real winners of life and what
actually matters in Life, role of our friends, family in a students life are also
discussed.
Sanket Palwe, Department of Engineering, Sciences and Humanities, VIT, Pune-37 11

content production in team, because in solo performance it is easy to
create script, and directly perform it. But in team we have to
brainstrom on every idea, design every scene, get corrected from

emotion to be potrayed to audience.
